  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">10</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">The horizon-radius of a (D + 1)-dimensional Schwarzschild black hole of mass M is given by [11] rH = [16πM/(D - 1) ˆAD-1] 1/(D-2), where ˆAD-1 = 2πD/2 /Γ(D/2) is the generalized area of a unit (D - 1)-sphere</subfield>
  </datafield>
